  <p>
    After seeing strong interest from around the company when Instacart engineers ran internal sessions about SQL and basic web development, a few of us started to talk about using our love of teaching and mentoring to offer something like a full-fledged coding bootcamp. This program would take someone with little coding background and prepare them for an entry level software engineering role at a company like Instacart.
  </p>
  <h3 class="cu-header">Class Is In Session</h3>
  <p>So what does day to day life at CarrotU actually look like?
  <p>The program runs for 4 months from kick off to graduation, with the expectation that students commit about 20 hours a week to the work, above their existing responsibilities at the company.
  <p>Every week students work through Treehouse videos and exercises, in addition to building custom projects specific to the CarrotU curriculum. There are live lectures once a week lead by one of the engineer mentors or a guest speaker from another part of the company such as design or product.

  <p>Near the end of the program, more of the work revolves around building a capstone project. This is a single project worked on by all the students in the program. The capstone project allows students to get experience working on a shared code base and doing project planning with other engineers.</p>
